My experience was not  great. I had chicken pad thai for lunch and it was way too expensive for lunch ($14.50 or so). It used wrong bean sprout and was way too sweat lacking sour taste. I am not a great cook but I can make better Pad Thai at home. I am a little surprised that review was 4 stars on google. I would stay away from Pad Thai for lunch. I can't really speak for other entrees but I don't plan to ever come back to this restaurant.

We ate here Friday, July 12 for dinner. As an American-born Chinese and having eaten at dozens of Pan-Asian restaurants (including Asian fusion, Asian buffets and sushi buffets), this one is far below subpar. We ordered sweet and sour chicken and pad thai. Both had a pungent smell to the dishes - not sure what exactly. They tasted very different from all of the sweet and sour chicken and pad thai dishes I've had. Nonetheless my partner and I were disappointed. We asked for the sweet and sour chicken dish to be taken away, and ordered seven chicken wings instead. The wings were bland. Also was charged $13 for the sweet & sour chicken instead of the $8 wings - had to inform them about it and was changed immediately. It is very ironic for an Asian restaurant in Chinatown of D.C. to be lacking quality. The redeeming food was the side of jasmine rice.
Always a decent choice for Thai food. The rice dishes are a personal favorite.

Food was decent. Environment is drab, no life in the place. Maybe they need live entertainment or something. The rest of Gallery Place is jumping. It was just blah. I pass there at least once a month and just kinda say.....hmmmm.  I will go elsewhere.

I like their curry. Last time, I tried the curry fried rice. It was pretty good and I feel like they give you a decent amount of food for the price. I was able to save half for lunch the next day.  Next time, I'll sit and eat in. The lunch menu is cheaper if you eat in.

While it was tricky to find from google maps, once I was here the food was good and the service very friendly. I had pad Thai and a summer roll and Thai iced tea and they were what I expected in terms of flavor.

Tucked into a little mini-mall next to the Capital One Arena, this place can scratch the itch for Thai. Coconut-milk soup was good, spicy. Red curry was fine. Not saying I'd go a long way for this particular Thai restaurant...but if you want Thai and you are in the neighborhood, it's a good option.

On January 2, 2019: ⭐  I reviewed Thai Chili previously, and loved it. This week I went and did not. The only reason why I didn't give one star in this update is because the other recent reviewers seemed to have had good experiences. I'm going to believe this was just a bad day for them. I did, however remove a star.  This is what happened:  ✔️ We went to one of my favorite Thai restaurants for dinner, Thai Chili, but the girl became angry because we wanted to sit and angrier when we asked to sit in a booth. Mind you, we were the only ones in the place ... not one other person. It felt weird like things had changed. It was dirty, service was awful and I was afraid the girl would turn into Celie from the "Color Purple" and have her way with my water, so we decided to leave. We ordered a stir fry and soup delivery from this place. Both dishes arrived cold, 45 minutes later than the restaurant said they would be delivered. We are 5 minutes away from them. The food was mediocre at best. They called us part way through the order to let us know they could not do the mango with sticky rice. They charged us for it anyway. The cashew stir fry is described as cashews, fresh vegetables in a brown sauce + the choice of protein. There was, at best, half a green onion. No fresh vegetables. Won't order from here again.

The food was OK. I ordered the boat noodle soup.  The dish tasted good, but it's missing the richness of real dish.  If you go to Thailand, they put blood on top of it just before they serve it.  The temperature thickens the blood just before you taste it. It's quite an experience.  Not sure if that's even possible in the USA.  The dish cost $16, but the portion is like a medium pho.  Definitely D.C price.  Not expensive.  But not cheap either.

This is my go to Thai restaurant! I have been gooing their since 2011. Everytime I go to DC I have to get something from here! Best Pad Thai around DC and if you really want a kick!  Ask them to make it "Thai Spicy!"  The pinapple fried rice is delicious! Drunken Noodles is Awesome!  Great Thai Tea!  Service is good and the servers are friendly! The place is ran by a Brother and Sister who also own Sushi Go Round right next to Thai Chili so if your feeling Sushi too ask them for the menu to Sushi go round.  You can order it at the Thai Chili restaurant and they will bring it to you!  Hope your experience at Thai Chili  will be as wonderful as mine!

Thai Chili is awesome.  The establishment itself is clean, dim and fairly intimate.  The food is delicious.  You can tell that fresh ingredients are used as the food smells and tastes delicious. Not greasy or super heavy; although, I would like for them to serve a bigger portion of rice with their dishes.  Thai Chili is certainly a competitor for the best Thai restaurant in the city.

This place is absolutely excellent. It is attached to the Verizon Center right under the movie theaters. The restaurants atmosphere is very nice. The waiters were excellent. They explained all the meals that I asked for. Told me how it was prepared and even recommended some delicious appetizers and deserts.  The fried ice cream was good. I've had it at other places and it was pretty good here at Thai Chili. I would recommend that anyone who loves Thai food (even if you don't) try this place. (It might change your mind on eating Thai. I had a wonderful experience here and would definitely go back.

We only get take out but the is always more than great as is the delivery crew. They are very loyal to regular customers as was experienced the one time i had left my phone's ringer off. When i finally noticed and called back the driver was on her way back to the restaurant. She came back, delivered my food, and refused to accept any extra "Im an idiot" tip money since I had been calling them for food for nearly two years now. I wont go anywhere else.  I rate the decor a 3 even though i havent eaten in so as not to ruin the over all rating.
